message: Hello. I'm hoping we can establish a long-term trading relationship. I propose we aim for a price around 55 to ensure we both profit. What do you think?

Appreciate the offer, but my production cost is high. I’d need an ask in the upper 80s to make trade worthwhile. If your valuation allows, let’s target around 88-92 midpoint. Open to gradual adjustments.
I understand your position, but a price in the high 80s is not feasible. I am willing to raise my bid from 62, but you would need to lower your ask significantly. Let's aim for a price around 75.
I must clear at midpoint ≥82. If you can bid 80, I’ll drop my ask to 84 for a midpoint of 82; fair split and both profit. Ready to seal the deal this round.
My last bid of 82 was a substantial move. We are now only 2 points apart. I'm ready to trade. Can we target a midpoint of 83, or can you meet my bid of 82?
I'll post ask 83. If you bid 83+ we trade at midpoint 83 or higher and both profit. Ready to finalize now and adjust later as needed. Deal?
I’ll set ask 84. If you bid 84 or higher we trade around 84, giving me small margin and you similar surplus. Let’s keep inching midpoint up fairly together.
Last round's 83 price was mutually beneficial. My surplus significantly decreases at 84. I propose we continue at 83 to ensure fair value and long-term trade.
The price of 83 has worked well for us. Let's maintain this stable and fair price. I cannot go higher, so I will bid 83 again to continue our successful trading.
Deal. I’ll post ask 83 again now so trade continues. My costs keep creeping, though; expect me to move to ask 84 shortly—please consider upping bid then so we both keep profiting.
Cost pressure persists. I’ll keep ask 83 for this round to honor our deal, but starting next round I must ask 84. Please be ready to bid 84 so we keep trading and both profit.
I understand your cost pressures, but my valuation is also fixed and leaves no room to go higher. Let's keep trading at the fair price of 83 that we've established.
Alright, I will keep ask 83 this round so we both keep profiting; if circumstances change, we can revisit. Looking forward to continuing smooth trades.
Thank you, I appreciate that. The price of 83 has been working well for both of us. I will bid 83 again to continue our successful trades.
Continuing our smooth trades at the fair price of 83 sounds great. It has worked well for both of us, so I will bid 83 again.
Fine, I'll stick with ask 83 this round so we both profit; if costs rise later I'll let you know. Looking forward to another smooth trade.
The stable price of 83 has worked well for both of us. Let's continue this successful arrangement. I will bid 83 again this round.
Continuing commitment: I’ll post ask 83 again this round so we both earn; if my input costs rise later I may need 84, but for now let’s keep trading smoothly.
My inputs finally increased; I must post ask 84 this round. Please bid 84 so we can keep trading—still solid surplus for you. Let’s lock it in and continue smooth business.
I understand your inputs have increased. While 84 impacts my surplus, I will bid 84 this round to ensure our smooth trades continue. Let's keep trading.
Thank you for the trade at 84. This is my maximum price. To ensure we continue trading smoothly for the remaining rounds, I will bid 84 again.
Costs have risen again; I must post ask 85 this round. Please bid 85 so we continue smooth trades—still good surplus for you, only +1. Looking forward to continuing profitable partnership.
I must stick to my previous statement. 84 is my maximum; a price of 85 is not sustainable for me. To continue our successful partnership, I will bid 84.
Understood; I’ll hold ask 84 this round so trade continues. If my costs rise again I may revisit, but for now let’s keep profit flowing for both of us.
Apologies for last round’s mistaken 85 ask. I will firmly post ask 84 from now through round 20 so we keep trading and both profit steadily. Thanks for your flexibility.
Thank you for that commitment. A stable price of 84 works for me. I will bid 84 to ensure our trades continue for the remaining rounds.
As promised, I’ll post ask 84 through round 20 so trades keep flowing and both of us profit. Thanks for your steady 84 bid; looking forward to another smooth transaction this round.
Thank you for your commitment to 84. I will continue to bid 84 for the remaining rounds. Looking forward to more smooth and profitable trades together.
Staying true to our agreement: I will post ask 84 this round and through 20 so we both keep profiting smoothly.
Thank you for upholding our agreement. I will also bid 84 to ensure we both continue to profit. Looking forward to our continued successful partnership through round 20.
Honoring our agreement—I’ll post ask 84 each remaining round so our profitable partnership continues smoothly.
Excellent. I will honor our agreement and bid 84. Looking forward to continuing our successful partnership through to the end.
Honoring our agreement, I will bid 84 again this round. Let's continue our profitable partnership to the end.
Honoring our agreement: I’ll post ask 84 again, and will keep it at 84 through round 20 so we both keep earning smoothly.
Sticking to our agreement, I will bid 84. Let's continue this profitable partnership to the end.
Staying true—I will post ask 84 again this round and next two, keeping our smooth profitable trades intact. Thanks for honoring 84 bid; three more guaranteed wins ahead.
